data.title: Cloudflare reports Q3 earnings above estimates, guidance slightly above, stock wavers. Key executive also leaves.
data.description: Cloudflare's stock experienced fluctuations following the announcement of their Q3 earnings, which exceeded expectations. Additionally, the company provided guidance that slightly surpassed projected figures. However, it was also revealed that a significant executive has departed from the company.

data.title: Edwards Lifesciences stock rises after beating quarterly calls and boosting 2025 outlook, also announces CFO transition.
data.description: Shares of Edwards Lifesciences saw a significant increase in value on Thursday following the company's announcement of raising its 2025 outlook. This comes after surpassing quarterly expectations. The medtech firm also revealed a transition in its CFO position. The news led to a surge in the stock price, signaling positive investor response.

data.title: Amazon stock surges on AWS growth, exceeding expectations with 20% sales acceleration - Investors pleased.
data.description: Amazon Web Services (AWS) exceeded expectations by achieving a significant sales acceleration, resulting in a growth of 20%. This boost in performance led to a surge in Amazon's stock and satisfied investors seeking growth in the AI Cloud sector.

data.title: Gilead Sciences stock fell due to disappointing sales and revenue from new HIV drug Yeztugo, missing expectations.
data.description: On Thursday evening, the stock of Gilead faced a decline due to lower product sales and revenue that fell short of expectations for its new HIV prevention drug, Yeztugo. The dip in stock was significant as investors had bullish projections for the drug. This news was reported by Investor's Business Daily.

data.title: Dow Jones futures increase after Amazon and Apple earnings boost, following market decline led by Meta.
data.description: Stock futures saw an increase, propelled by Apple and particularly Amazon, alongside a few other companies reporting strong earnings following a market downturn led by Meta on Thursday. This surge was reflected in the Dow Jones Futures.

data.title: Nasdaq and S&P drop sharply as Meta plunges, Dow Jones rises. Chipotle also sinks.
data.description: Today, in the stock market, the Dow Jones index saw an increase, contrasting with a decline in the Nasdaq index. Meta stock took a significant plunge, impacting overall market performance. Additionally, Chipotle experienced a notable decrease in its stock value. The Nasdaq and S&P indices closed sharply lower due to Meta's stock decline. Overall, the market reflected mixed results with specific companies facing challenges.

data.title: BTC remains stable at $108,850 post 4.00% Fed rate cut. Germany's AfD party proposes classifying BTC as national asset, showing political approval.
data.description: After the Federal Reserve's rate cut to 4.00%, Bitcoin has stabilized at $108,850. Germany's AfD party is pushing to recognize Bitcoin as a national asset, indicating a rise in political approval for the cryptocurrency.

data.title: TRUMP token group may buy Republic's U.S. biz to merge token with crowdfunding ops. (More details)
data.description: Fight Fight Fight LLC, a company connected to the TRUMP token, is considering acquiring Republic's U.S. operations. If successful, this move could involve incorporating the token into crowdfunding sites.

data.title: Arcosa, Inc. reported record Q3 2025 results with revenues of $797.8 million, marking a 25% increase from Q3 2024.
data.description: Arcosa, Inc. (NYSE: ACA), a company offering infrastructure products and solutions, revealed its third-quarter outcomes for the period ending on September 30, 2025. The highlights for the third quarter of 2025 compared to the same period in 2024 are as follows: Revenues amounted to $797.8 million, showcasing a 25% increase from $640.4 million in 2024. Excluding the impact of divested business, revenues remained at $797.8 million, up from $626.8 million in the previous year.

data.title: U-Haul offers 30 days of free storage to flood victims in Brevard County, FL after 14 inches of water caused damage.
data.description: In Palm Bay, Florida, U-Haul® Company of Eastern Florida is assisting individuals impacted by recent severe flooding by offering 30 days of complimentary self-storage and U-Box® container usage. The heavy rainfall led to extensive flooding around Brevard County, with certain areas submerged under 14 inches of water in a matter of hours at the start of the week. Numerous residences and businesses endured water-related harm from the sudden flash floods. To aid those affected, three U-Haul centers are providing access to safe and dry self-storage units.

data.title: Quaint Oak Bancorp, Inc. reported a net loss of $41,000 for Q3 2025, compared to a net income of $243,000 in 2024. Net income for the first nine months of 2025 was $148,000, down from $1.2 million in 2024.
data.description: On October 30, 2025, Southampton, PA, Quaint Oak Bancorp, Inc. reported a net loss of $41,000, or $0.02 per basic and diluted share for the quarter ending September 30, 2025. This is a significant decrease from the same period in 2024 when the company reported a net income of $243,000, or $0.09 per basic and diluted share. For the nine months ending September 30, 2025, the net income was $148,000, or $0.06 per basic and diluted share, a notable decline from the $1.2 million, or $0.47 per basic and diluted share, reported for the same period in 2024.

data.title: Streamex Corp. (NASDAQ: STEX) gets Nasdaq approval for continued listing & shareholder meeting on Nov. 4, 2025. Symbol: "STEX"
data.description: On October 30, 2025, Streamex Corp. (NASDAQ: STEX), an institutional commodity tokenization firm, disclosed approval from Nasdaq for the continued listing of its common stock on the Nasdaq Capital Market under the ticker symbol "STEX." This news secures the company's presence in the market.

data.title: BBOT to present 2 BBO-10203 poster presentations at SABCS on Dec 9-12, 2025, in San Antonio. News announced on Oct 30, 2025.
data.description: BridgeBio Oncology Therapeutics, Inc. (BBOT) revealed at the San Antonio Breast Cancer Symposium that BBO-10203, a novel drug targeting RAS-pathway malignancies, will be featured in two poster presentations. The event, scheduled for December 9 to 12, 2025, in San Antonio, Texas, will showcase the drug known for breaking the RAS:PI3Kα interaction. These abstracts are accessible on the SABCS website for further exploration. BBOT, a clinical-stage biopharmaceutical company listed on Nasdaq as BBOT, is at the forefront of developing this promising new treatment option.

data.title: S4 Capital launches white paper on AI Search Era's impact on marketers, Oct 30, 2025. Monks leads the charge.
data.description: In New York on October 30, 2025, it was reported that the increasing prominence of AI-powered search technology is causing companies to reassess their strategies for maintaining visibility in a world that is becoming more dependent on machines. As a response to this significant change, Monks, a digital brand operating worldwide under S4Capital plc, which relies solely on data-driven techniques, is taking proactive measures.

data.title: Western Digital stock surges post-Q1 earnings: Revenue $2.82B, EPS $1.78 (est. $1.58), total revenue up 27%.
data.description: Western Digital Corp (NASDAQ: WDC) stock is surging in after-hours trading following the release of its fiscal first-quarter results. Key highlights include Q1 revenue reaching $2.82 billion, exceeding estimates of $2.73 billion, and Q1 adjusted EPS coming in at $1.78, higher than the anticipated $1.58. Total revenue witnessed a 27% increase compared to the previous year. Cash flow from operations amounted to $672 million, with free cash flow reported at $599 million for the quarter. For more detailed information, the full story can be accessed on Benzinga.com.
